## 4. Thesis Recommendations & Next Steps

This dataset is perfect for your **Objective 2 (Mapping Geomorphic Features)** and **Objective 3 (Spatiotemporal Relationships)**:

1. **Objective 2 (Shoreline Change Rate):** 
   You can report that the Cape Coast shoreline is split: **52.4% is eroding** (max rate: $-1.26\text{ m/yr}$) and **47.6% is accreting** (max rate: $+1.53\text{ m/yr}$). The mean rate of change is $+0.03\text{ m/yr}$.
2. **Objective 3 (Overlay with LULC):** 
   We can overlay these 187 transects with your LULC maps to see if areas with high urban built-up expansion near the coast correlate with higher shoreline erosion rates (due to destruction of natural sand buffers, seawall construction, or runoff).
